
Indeed Job Scraper (IBScraper) (Indeed 🚀Blast Scraper)

Overview
IBScraper is a powerful, automated web scraping tool designed to fetch job listings from Indeed.com. It leverages AI to intelligently filter and rank jobs based on their relevance to your resume, saving you hours/day of manual searching. The scraper is built with stealth in mind, using advanced techniques like browser fingerprinting and proxies to avoid detection.

The final output is neatly organized into a local Excel file and can be automatically uploaded and sorted in a Google Sheet for easy access and collaboration.

Key Features

Multi-threaded Scraping: Processes multiple job search queries concurrently for maximum speed.

AI-Powered Resume Matching: Uses a Groq AI model (Llama 3) to calculate a match percentage for each job against your resume, ensuring you only see the most relevant opportunities.

Advanced Stealth: Bypasses bot detection using unique browser fingerprints, proxies, and human-like browser interactions.

Cloudflare Bypass: Integrated with 2Captcha to automatically solve Cloudflare Turnstile challenges.

Smart Filtering:

Ignores a comprehensive list of pre-defined companies (e.g., large corporations, staffing agencies).

Avoids scraping duplicate jobs from previous runs.

Limits the number of jobs scraped per company to diversify results.

Organized Data Export:

Saves job details to a local Excel file (.xlsx).

Categorizes jobs into three sheets: Easy_applies, CS_applies (Company Site), and Confirmation_applies (high-priority companies).

Automatically uploads and sorts the data in a designated Google Sheet.

Highly Configurable: Easily customize search queries, filtering criteria, and AI prompts through a central configuration file.

How It Works (Workflow)

The scraper follows a systematic process to fetch, filter, and save job data:

Initialization:

Loads all settings from config_input.py and scraper_setting.py.

Loads proxies, Indeed account cookies, and browser fingerprints.

Loads the list of already processed jobs to prevent duplicates.

Listing Scraper:

Launches a separate, isolated browser instance for each search URL in jobs_listed_pages_urls.

Each instance is configured with a unique proxy, account, and fingerprint.

Navigates through the job search result pages, collecting job titles, company names, and links.

Filters out jobs from ignored companies or those already processed.

AI Matching:

Batches the collected job titles and sends them to the Groq AI API along with your resume.

The AI returns a match percentage for each job.

Detail Scraper:

For jobs that meet the MATCHING_PERCENTAGE threshold, the scraper opens each job link in a new tab.

It extracts full details: company name, job title, salary, description, benefits, etc.

It categorizes the job based on the application type ("Easy Apply" vs. "Apply on company site").

Data Storage:

The categorized job data is appended to the corresponding sheets in the local output/jobs.xlsx file.

Finally, the data from the Excel file is uploaded to your configured Google Sheet, sorted by match percentage in descending order.

Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following:

Python 3.8+

An account with Groq AI to get an API key.

An account with 2Captcha to get an API key for solving CAPTCHAs.

One or more Indeed.com accounts.

A Google Cloud Platform (GCP) project with the Google Sheets API enabled and a service account credentials.json file.

Access to HTTP Proxies.

