Configure Google Sheets:

Go to your GCP project, create a service account, and download its JSON key.

Rename the downloaded file to gs_credentials.json and place it in the root directory.

Open your target Google Sheet and share it with the client_email found inside the gs_credentials.json file, giving it "Editor" permissions.

Add Proxies:
Edit the proxies.txt file and add your proxies, one per line, in the format ip:port:username:password.

Add Indeed Accounts:

Log in to an Indeed account in your browser.

Use a cookie editor extension (like EditThisCookie) to export your cookies as a JSON file.

Place the JSON file(s) in the accounts/ directory. Each file represents one account.

Add Browser Fingerprints:
Place your browser fingerprint JSON files in the fingerprints/ directory. The scraper uses these to appear as a unique, real user for each session.

Configuration (config_input.py)

This is the main file for customizing the scraper's behavior.

jobs_listed_pages_urls: A Python list of Indeed search result URLs. Each URL represents a query the scraper will process.
Example: "https://www.indeed.com/jobs?q=python+developer&l=United+States&fromage=1"

MATCHING_PERCENTAGE: An integer (0-100). The scraper will only fetch full details for jobs with an AI match score equal to or greater than this value.
Example: 60

leave_blank_colls: An integer. Inserts a specified number of empty columns in the output Excel/Google Sheet, useful for adding manual notes.
Example: 2

confirmation_companies: A list of company names. Jobs from these companies are always saved to the "Confirmation_applies" sheet, regardless of application type, for high-priority review.

AI_PROMPT & RESUME:

AI_PROMPT: The template text sent to the AI. It instructs the model on how to format its response.

RESUME: A concise, keyword-rich summary of your skills and experience. The AI uses this to calculate the match score.

per_company_jobs: An integer. Sets the maximum number of jobs to process from a single company during a run to ensure a diverse set of results.
Example: 3

ignore_companies: A comprehensive list of company names to completely ignore. This is pre-populated with major tech companies, staffing agencies, and government entities to filter out noise. You can add or remove companies as needed.

Running the Scraper

Create Initial Files: Before the first run, create an empty Excel file by running helper.create_wb_with_3sheet(). You can do this by adding helper.create_wb_with_3sheet() to a temporary script or main.py and running it once.

Start the Scraper:
Execute the main script from your terminal.

Generated bash
python main.py
